# Using useEffect in React

`useEffect` is a React Hook that lets you perform side effects in functional components.

## Basic Syntax

```javascript
useEffect(() => {
  // Your side effect here
  return () => {
    // Optional cleanup function
  }
}, [dependencies])
```

## Common Use Cases

1. **Data Fetching**
```javascript
useEffect(() => {
  fetchData().then(data => setData(data))
}, [])
```

2. **Event Listeners**
```javascript
useEffect(() => {
  window.addEventListener('resize', handleResize)
  return () => window.removeEventListener('resize', handleResize)
}, [])
```

3. **Reacting to prop changes**
```javascript
useEffect(() => {
  document.title = `Count: ${count}`
}, [count])
```

# CSS Flexbox Examples

## 1. Center Content

```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
  height: 100vh;
}
```

## 2. Three Column Layout

```css
.row {
  display: flex;
  gap: 20px;
}

.column {
  flex: 1;
}
```

## 3. Sticky Footer

```css
.layout {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  min-height: 100vh;
}

.content {
  flex: 1;
}
```

## 4. Responsive Card Grid

```css
.grid {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 1rem;
}

.card {
  flex: 1 1 300px;
}
```

## 5. Equal Height Columns

```css
.container {
  display: flex;
}

.column {
  flex: 1;
}
```

Flexbox makes one-dimensional layouts simple and responsive!
